A node is identified by an id.
A color is identified by an id.
A connected_to is identified by a firstnode, and by a secondnode.
An assigned_to is identified by a node, and by a color.
It is prohibited that there is a connected_to with firstnode X, with secondnode Y, whenever there is a node with id X, whenever there is a assigned_to with node id X, with color id C, whenever there is a node with id Y, whenever there is a assigned_to with node id Y, with color id C, whenever there is a color with id C.
